CL-FIBER is a simple API for creating cooperative multithreads. It is
based on cl-cont and uses delimited continuations to form fibers. The
API is fashioned after SB-THREAD and has similar public interface.

Author:

  Valentin Pavlov <x.pavlov@gmail.com>

License:

  MIT-style. See file LICENSE.txt for details.

Bugs and Issues:

  None yet, this is an early beta release, not tested enough.

